				<h1>Adult Nursing services </h1>
				<h2>One-on-one nursing with compassion, excellence, and reliability in the comfort of home</h2>
				<!--#include virtual="/includes/jose-story.inc"-->
				<p><span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#AdultNursing">Adult Nursing</a> services help adults of all ages with ongoing care needs related to chronic illness, injury, or disability. These needs range from the management of conditions like diabetes to complex, high-tech <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#Tracheostomy">tracheostomy</a> and <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#Ventilator">ventilator</a> nursing care.</p>
				<p>These services are provided by registered nurses (RNs) and licensed practical nurses (LPNs) primarily on an ongoing shift (two-hour or more) basis, and are available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. This care is also sometimes referred to as private duty or adult skilled nursing.</p>
				<p>All <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Nurses are home health care specialists. Our RNs and LPNs are highly experienced and knowledgeable professionals who are committed to providing quality, compassionate care to their clients and peace of mind for their families.</p>

				<h2>A broad range of nursing services</h2>

				<p>We can provide a wide variety of nursing services, including:</p>
					<ul>
				                <li>Administering and monitoring medication</li>
				                <li>Pain management</li>
				                <li>Diabetes management</li>
				                <li>Cancer care</li>
				                <li>Cardiac care </li>
				                <li>Blood pressure management</li>
				                <li>Bowel and bladder management</li>
				                <li>Catheter care</li>
				                <li>Ostomy care</li>
				                <li>Respiratory care</li>
				                <li>Tracheostomy and ventilator nursing care</li>
				                <li>Alzheimer’s and dementia management</li>
				                <li>Neurological disease management</li>
	            			</ul><br>

	            		<h2>Quality care you can trust</h2>

	            		<p><span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> takes extra steps to ensure clinical excellence and safety:</p>
	            			<ul>
				            	<li><span class="bold">Rigorous hiring standards.</span> Like all <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> health care professionals, our nurses undergo an in-depth interview process, with thorough background checks and work history verification.</li>
				            	<li><span class="bold">Ongoing supervision and training.</span> All aspects of your care plan are overseen by a clinical manager who is a registered nurse and makes routine supervisory visits. We assess your care team’s skills on a regular basis and provide ongoing training and education, so they always know the latest treatment practices and technologies.</li>
				            	<li><span class="bold">Client and family-centered team approach.</span> Our nurses partner with you in your care. We communicate regularly with you, your family caregivers, your physician, and your care team.</li>
				            	<li><span class="bold">Commitment to our core values.</span> All our nurses are committed to providing care with compassion, excellence, and reliability&mdash;it's <span class="italics"><a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#BayadaWay">The <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Way</a></span>.</li>
	            			</ul>

				<!-- definitions (hidden) -->
				<div id="AdultNursing" class="define-word"><p>Adult nursing is a <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Home Health Care specialty practice. It refers to care provided by registered or licensed practical nurses at home for adults and seniors dealing with chronic illness, injury, or disability. <a href="glossary-a.asp#AdultNursing">Read full adult nursing definition...</a></p></div>

				<div id="Tracheostomy" class="define-word"><p>A tracheostomy is a surgically-created opening in the trachea on the surface of the neck where a metal or plastic tube is inserted to assist with breathing. This tube is secured with flexible ties that are fastened around the neck.</p></div>

				<div id="Ventilator" class="define-word"><p>A ventilator is a mechanical device that performs the function of inflating, and in some cases deflating a person’s lungs at preset intervals.</p></div>

				<div id="BayadaWay" class="define-word"><p>Our company philosophy, <span class="italics">The <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Way</span> expresses the values and beliefs that have been the foundation of our work since 1975. The words of The <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Way come directly from our clients and their families, and our employees. We believe that our clients come first and our employees are our greatest asset.</p></div>
